	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64623211"><p>It's interesting to look at the progression of storage media that everyone thought would be perfect for long-term archiving.  How many of these technologies still survive and is the hardware still made for it today?  Every time a new technology rises to the top, it's eventually surpassed by something else.  Are any of them completely bullet proof i.e. they will still be readable in 10, 20, 50 years or more from now?</p></div>
	</div>

